{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "label": "Provider adapter pattern (contract.ts + concrete impl + barrel)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Canonical shape for adding a provider adapter: src/lib/adapters/<name>/ with contract.ts interface, one concrete implementation, and an index.ts barrel."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_auth_adapter", "label": "Auth adapter (src/lib/adapters/auth/, better-auth.ts)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_email_adapter", "label": "Email adapter (src/lib/adapters/email/, EMAIL_PROVIDER=log default)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_billing_adapter", "label": "Billing adapter (src/lib/adapters/billing/, stripe.ts + none.ts default)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Default provider must never throw at construction because the factory runs at module load and would break next build for anyone without that vendor configured."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_jobs_adapter_transactional_outbox", "label": "Jobs adapter / transactional outbox (enqueue writes row, drain executes)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "enqueue(writer, ...) always writes a row within the caller's transaction; the adapter drains separately (postgres executes, hosted scheduler forwards). Letting a hosted adapter's enqueue call its own SDK directly destroys atomicity because an HTTP call cannot roll back."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_admin_auth_adapter", "label": "AdminAuthAdapter (superadmin/user role vocabulary, translated at boundary)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Better Auth stores the super-admin flag as user.role; the contract exposes plain isSuperAdmin derived at the boundary so UI and engine cannot disagree. adminUserIds must never be set (bypasses permission checks). Reads belong in features/admin/data.ts, not the adapter."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_rate_limit_adapter", "label": "Rate-limit adapter (atomic INSERT ... ON CONFLICT counter, fails open)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two racing requests must serialize against each other, not a caller's write, so there is no writer parameter; decide vs decideNext are two separate helpers to avoid off-by-one limits; a throwing store fails open (allowed:true, warn log) so a DB blip does not become a total outage."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_i18n_translation_pattern", "label": "Translate a string pattern (useTranslations/getTranslations, en.json/pl.json compile-checked)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "MESSAGES is Record<Locale, typeof en>, so a missing pl.json key is a compile error; getTranslator(locale, ns) is used outside a request (cron/email) since request-scoped hooks throw there."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_proxy_locale_routing", "label": "Locale routing in src/proxy.ts (next-intl middleware never imported)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two systems cannot both own the response, so auth default-deny and locale prefixing are composed by hand in one file with one documented ordering; localePrefix:always keeps the proxy redirect-only so the guarded path equals the served path."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_logging_pattern", "label": "Structured logging pattern (createLogger, no-console ESLint rule)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Message is a constant, everything variable is a field; err is reserved for the caught Error so the stack survives; requestLogger seeds request-scoped context, plain createLogger for jobs via AsyncLocalStorage; LOG_FORMAT=json in production for a collector."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_background_job_pattern", "label": "Add a background job pattern (JobName/JobPayloads, registry, enqueueJob)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Pass tx as writer whenever a job accompanies a business write for atomic commit/rollback; handlers must be idempotent (dedupeKey) since the queue is at-least-once; payloads are JSON and zod-parsed on the way out; a no-op is success, not failure."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_email_template_pattern", "label": "Add an email template pattern (TemplateName/TemplateProps, enqueueEmail single delivery path)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Never call email.send directly; enqueueEmail is the single delivery path keeping retry, suppression, List-Unsubscribe centralized. Templates are plain JSX rendered by @react-email/render for HTML + plain-text."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_tenant_isolated_entity_pattern", "label": "Add a tenant-isolated entity pattern (indexed owner column, owner-scoped data layer)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The two tenant owners are personal_account and organization; membership/invitation carry an indexed organizationId and every read/write is scoped by it in the feature data layer - never query a tenant table without its owner filter."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_audit_state_change_pattern", "label": "Audit a state change pattern (AUDIT_ACTIONS, recordAudit(tx, ...), resolveActor)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "organizationId is a required audit field; actor comes from resolveActor(session) so impersonated actions attribute to the admin; changed(before, after, fields) returns undefined on a no-op so nothing is logged."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_ui_primitive_pattern", "label": "Add a UI primitive pattern (src/components/ui, semantic tokens, cva, Radix wrapping)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Style only with semantic tokens, never raw colors; compose classes with cn() so callers can override; interactive/overlay primitives wrap Radix for free focus management and ARIA."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_auth_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_email_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_billing_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_jobs_adapter_transactional_outbox", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_admin_auth_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_rate_limit_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_adapter_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_01_brak_vendor_lock_in", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_admin_auth_adapter", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_auth_adapter", "relation": "shares_data_with", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_admin_auth_adapter", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_06_dostep_super_admin", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/a-adaptery-i18n-zadania-dane-audyt.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_r